{"name":"Weapon Properties","pages":[{"sort":100000,"name":"Thrown","type":"text","_id":"eRNJUSk3reKEHB2j","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p><span style=\"font-family:Signika, sans-serif\">If a weapon has the thrown property, you can throw the weapon to make a ranged attack. If the weapon is a melee weapon, you use the same ability modifier for that attack roll and damage roll that you would use for a melee attack with the weapon. For example, if you throw a handaxe, you use your Strength, but if you throw a dagger, you can use either your Strength or your Dexterity, since the dagger has the finesse property.</span></p>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}},{"sort":200000,"name":"Light","type":"text","_id":"oWfwDQJ5AhxqvIDh","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p><span style=\"font-family:Signika, sans-serif\">A light weapon is small and easy to handle, making it ideal for use when fighting with two weapons.</span></p>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}},{"sort":300000,"name":"Two-Handed","type":"text","_id":"Gu8LqNh8i44XOFIc","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p><span style=\"font-family:Signika, sans-serif\">This weapon requires two hands when you attack with it.</span></p>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}},{"sort":0,"name":"Ammunition","type":"text","_id":"Y51hg0UV3eUclKWh","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p><span style=\"font-family:Signika, sans-serif\">To make a ranged attack with this weapon, you must expend one piece of ammunition. Drawing the ammunition from a quiver, case, or other container is part of the attack (you need a free hand to load a one-handed weapon). At the end of the battle, you can recover half your expended ammunition by taking a minute to search the battlefield. A weapon that has the ammunition property used to make a melee attack is treated as an improvised weapon. A sling must be loaded to deal any damage when used in this way.</span></p>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}},{"sort":50000,"name":"Adamantine","type":"text","_id":"bgd7kEKD11WsgWbJ","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p>Any weapon coated or made of Adamantine, one of the hardest substances in existance, will always critically strike when hitting an object.</p>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}},{"sort":400000,"name":"Finesse","type":"text","_id":"voMu63oWtk4tB4yS","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p><span style=\"font-family:Signika, sans-serif\">When making an attack with a finesse weapon, you use your choice of your Strength or Dexterity modifier for the attack and damage rolls. You must use the same modifier for both rolls.</span></p>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}},{"sort":500000,"name":"Heavy","type":"text","_id":"Tl3nOMovYkdAqwhz","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p><span style=\"font-family:Signika, sans-serif\">Small creatures have disadvantage on attack rolls with heavy weapons. A heavy weapon's size and bulk make it too large for a Small creature to use effectively.</span></p>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}},{"sort":600000,"name":"Light","type":"text","_id":"sC4f4yT3iq8ionZG","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p><span style=\"font-family:Signika, sans-serif\">A light weapon is small and easy to handle, making it ideal for use when fighting with two weapons.</span></p>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}},{"sort":700000,"name":"Loading","type":"text","_id":"TGVRkvB6r21CGy9V","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p><span style=\"font-family:Signika, sans-serif\">Because of the time required to load this weapon, you can fire only one piece of ammunition from it when you use an action, bonus action, or reaction to fire it, regardless of the number of attacks you can normally make.</span></p>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}},{"sort":800000,"name":"Range","type":"text","_id":"Cj8HR8ES9HlRei2N","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p><span style=\"font-family:Signika, sans-serif\">A weapon that can be used to make a ranged attack has a range in parentheses after the ammunition or thrown property. The range lists two numbers. The first is the weapon's normal range in feet, and the second indicates the weapon's long range. When attacking a target beyond normal range, you have disadvantage on the attack roll. You can't attack a target beyond the weapon's long range.</span></p>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}},{"sort":900000,"name":"Reach","type":"text","_id":"snXcknJqPGQeeSOF","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p><span style=\"font-family:Signika, sans-serif\">This weapon adds 5 feet to your reach when you attack with it, as well as when determining your reach for opportunity attacks with it.</span></p>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}},{"sort":1000000,"name":"Special","type":"text","_id":"danlbhQSPcM9hdhO","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p><span style=\"font-family:Signika, sans-serif\">A weapon with the special property has unusual rules governing its use, explained in the weapon's description.</span></p>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}},{"sort":1100000,"name":"Versatile","type":"text","_id":"BccgZwkUODMePyki","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p><span style=\"font-family:Signika, sans-serif\">This weapon can be used with one or two hands. A damage value in parentheses appears with the propertyâ€”the damage when the weapon is used with two hands to make a melee attack.</span></p>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}},{"sort":-100000,"name":"Instructions","type":"text","_id":"Rngb1j2gcYcaXpoK","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p><strong>READ ME: </strong>If you want to deviate from the module's provided default tooltips, change the source of the module's tooltips to your own copy of the properties in the module settings. Default is a journalentry in the Property Tooltip compendium, which you can copy and put somewhere else for a \"template\" to make your changes to. If you do not do this, every time the module gets updated, the module <em>will</em> overwrite any changes with no chance of recovery, unless you have a backup.</p><p>Create a separate page for each property you want to have a tooltip added to. The title must match the accompanying values in CONFIG.DND5E.weaponProperties. You can see below how that object looks like by default. The module searches for a tooltip description for abbreviations on the left, by searching through your set compendium source for the full name on the right. The default tooltips are my interpretation of the rules or lifted from the SRD, please check your rulebook(s) for accurate tooltips. </p><p><code>{</code></p><p><code>\"ada\": \"Adamantine\",</code></p><p><code>\"amm\": \"Ammunition\",</code></p><p><code>\"fin\": \"Finesse\",</code></p><p><code>\"fir\": \"Firearm\",</code></p><p><code>\"foc\": \"Focus\",</code></p><p><code>\"hvy\": \"Heavy\",</code></p><p><code>\"lgt\": \"Light\",</code></p><p><code>\"lod\": \"Loading\",</code></p><p><code>\"mgc\": \"Magical\",</code></p><p><code>\"rch\": \"Reach\",</code></p><p><code>\"rel\": \"Reload\",</code></p><p><code>\"ret\": \"Returning\",</code></p><p><code>\"sil\": \"Silvered\",</code></p><p><code>\"spc\": \"Special\",</code></p><p><code>\"thr\": \"Thrown\",</code></p><p><code>\"two\": \"Two-Handed\",</code></p><p><code>\"ver\": \"Versatile\"</code></p><p><code>}</code></p>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.13oUCdcsgiuKPJGY.JournalEntryPage.Rngb1j2gcYcaXpoK"}}},{"sort":1200000,"name":"Magical","type":"text","_id":"ok1PGaqIlr5DeSNv","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p>This weapon is considered magical for purposes of overcoming non-magical resistances.</p>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}},{"sort":1300000,"name":"Returning","type":"text","_id":"wH5QYuHq4xEZnH1T","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p><span style=\"font-family:Signika, sans-serif\">Immediately after making a ranged attack with this weapon, the weapon flies back to your hand.</span></p>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}},{"sort":1400000,"name":"Silvered","type":"text","_id":"M4UrssFWfP6ieE5P","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p>Some monsters that have immunity or resistance to nonmagical weapons are susceptible to silver weapons, so cautious adventurers invest extra coin to plate their weapons with silver. </p>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}},{"sort":1500000,"name":"Focus","type":"text","_id":"c2wItWi6nyirFLtk","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p>This weapon can be used as a spell focus for the purpose of casting spells with material components.</p>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}}],"ownership":{"default":0,"V5JIJaqwMD3QcCPN":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.13oUCdcsgiuKPJGY"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1681718701314,"modifiedTime":1681793534185,"lastModifiedBy":"92jQxldukRUpbwkL"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"CjhPaYRIDdcFd7No"}
